WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:42.820 --> 00:00:46.980
﻿Dejan, thank you for
your time with me.

00:00:47.460 --> 00:00:53.740
I find you in a good mood. In Hungary,
in Budapest, in Ferencvaros.

00:00:53.980 --> 00:00:58.500
You've been here for six months,
you have already acclimatized.

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:02.500
One transition period has passed.
How are you feeling?

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:06.740
What are your expectations?
-Thanks for the invitation.

00:01:06.940 --> 00:01:10.860
I responded with great pleasure
because I follow your work.

00:01:11.140 --> 00:01:15.580
I'm watching, listening to what you're
doing and you are doing amazing things.

00:01:15.780 --> 00:01:20.180
And once again, I want to congratulate
you on the whole organization.

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:23.380
Everything you imagined,
you achieved.

00:01:24.100 --> 00:01:27.780
I'm sure you won't dwell on it
and will move on.

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:32.140
I wish you all the best.
Now, I'm in Ferencvaros.

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:34.620
Budapest is my new chapter.

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:40.675
This club has a serious history
written for decades.

00:01:41.323 --> 00:01:45.060
This year is also the 125th anniversary
of Ferencvaros.

00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.420
Expectations are high.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:54.460
The new championship is moving
into its second part.

00:01:54.660 --> 00:01:58.580
Preparations were done
in phenomenal conditions.

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:04.300
Regarding the transition period,
they did what they promised.

00:02:04.580 --> 00:02:08.340
Have there been a lot of changes
in the transfer window?

00:02:08.580 --> 00:02:13.420
A lot of players came,
but they didn't stop there.

00:02:13.581 --> 00:02:16.500
Although Ferencvaros has won
the title for five years in a row,

00:02:16.643 --> 00:02:18.963
the management has not stopped.
They move on.

00:02:19.063 --> 00:02:21.328
They want a breakthrough
in Europe. -That's right.

00:02:21.498 --> 00:02:24.898
They want new players,
new targets.

00:02:25.106 --> 00:02:28.346
We have to do the most important thing
in order to have a starting point,

00:02:28.506 --> 00:02:30.483
which is winning the championship.

00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:34.740
I noticed that the new infrastructure
is perfect, as well as the new stadium.

00:02:35.020 --> 00:02:37.060
I wish you the best of luck.
-Thank you very much.

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:42.500
Now we'll go back to the beginnings.
To Zemun and you growing up.

00:02:42.740 --> 00:02:47.620
Your parents were
directly involved in football.

00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:55.540
What was the link and how did it all
start in Zemun? -Everything was nice.

00:02:55.780 --> 00:03:00.500
My parents were playing football
when they met and started dating.

00:03:00.753 --> 00:03:04.464
But when they got married
they stopped doing it.

00:03:04.605 --> 00:03:08.060
So I didn't have a chance...
Nor did they force me.

00:03:08.555 --> 00:03:12.755
Since I was little, that ball was
beginning and end of my day.

00:03:12.990 --> 00:03:18.926
I had a normal upbringing.
With good and strong attitudes.

00:03:20.293 --> 00:03:22.450
So I am grateful to them
for how they raised me.

00:03:22.629 --> 00:03:29.364
We all know how it was back then,
it's probably different now.

00:03:30.075 --> 00:03:35.675
Times change, but I'm so happy
with how I was raised in that home.

00:03:36.340 --> 00:03:44.540
And how I introduced myself
when I started playing football.

00:03:45.860 --> 00:03:49.220
And I passed all that
on to my children.

00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:52.860
I am very grateful to Bora
and Dragica for that.

00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:58.380
At that time there was a big dilemma
between folklore and football.

00:03:58.580 --> 00:04:03.100
Can you explain that to us?
I don't understand that analogy.

00:04:03.380 --> 00:04:06.420
Now when you look at me, you would
never say that I can do folklore.

00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:11.420
I'm like a stone, I'm a little
stronger and bigger.

00:04:12.300 --> 00:04:17.620
But I think that coordination had
a lot of influence later in my football.

00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:21.541
You think that helped you?
-I think so.

00:04:22.060 --> 00:04:29.180
It's something that taught me
about socializing and social life.

00:04:29.380 --> 00:04:31.780
That there are different people.

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:38.940
That there are people with
a different character. It was all fun.

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:44.180
I managed to go to both
football practice and folklore.

00:04:44.380 --> 00:04:48.380
How long did that last?
-Probably three or four years.

00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:54.380
That was serious then. -Yes, it was.
It lasted from my 12th to 16th year.

00:04:54.620 --> 00:04:57.660
Until I started playing
for the first team.

00:04:57.860 --> 00:05:00.770
After that I couldn't do it anymore.
-Of course you can't.

00:05:01.035 --> 00:05:06.995
That was a nice period
where I met a lot of people.

00:05:07.171 --> 00:05:11.331
I have also been on several trips
where I saw that there is

00:05:11.695 --> 00:05:17.015
something else besides football.

00:05:19.540 --> 00:05:24.740
Mother, apart from the specific fact
that she was involved in football,

00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:29.740
I read that she collected
everything related to you.

00:05:29.980 --> 00:05:33.820
From the first day... -When there were
no articles in the newspaper.

00:05:34.020 --> 00:05:41.660
Yes, you’re right. I have
12 or 13 notebooks in A4 format.

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.140
Those are some notes.

00:05:44.460 --> 00:05:48.980
Yes, about first games
when I started playing for Teleoptik.

00:05:49.180 --> 00:05:52.540
She wrote the date,
who we are playing against,

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:55.140
how I played and
what the score was.

00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:59.300
And so on until the age of 16.

00:05:59.540 --> 00:06:02.300
When it was no longer necessary.
-When newspaper clippings appeared.

00:06:02.540 --> 00:06:06.119
She collected every article
for every match, and I used

00:06:06.346 --> 00:06:09.380
that for my biography "Dejan".

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:15.540
Everyone used a lot of
that material and it is unique.

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:20.780
My parents didn't look at me
like a dollar or a walking euro.

00:06:21.060 --> 00:06:27.340
They just enjoyed it and supported me.
It wasn't always great and fabulous.

00:06:27.740 --> 00:06:34.660
They watched my every game.
Until I left Crvena Zvezda.

00:06:34.900 --> 00:06:38.537
When I started playing for the first team,
they didn't watch away games.

00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:42.717
But every game at the Maracana
until my last one they were there.

00:06:43.045 --> 00:06:47.646
Do you think that mom had
that maternal premonition

00:06:47.783 --> 00:06:52.943
that she was taking notes about a player
who would become the most decorated

00:06:53.072 --> 00:06:54.632
football player in Serbia?

00:06:54.980 --> 00:06:57.980
It is certain that mothers
feel something different.

00:06:58.260 --> 00:07:02.220
You think she knew that from
the beginning? -I can't say for sure.

00:07:02.660 --> 00:07:06.900
But I think mothers sense a lot of it.

00:07:07.140 --> 00:07:09.460
Sometimes they say it,
sometimes they don't.

00:07:09.653 --> 00:07:13.249
It all happened spontaneously
and was written with a lot of love.

00:07:13.406 --> 00:07:16.788
With a lot of faith.
Without any pushing or forcing.

00:07:16.948 --> 00:07:19.858
Maybe there is a secret
of success hidden in that.

00:07:25.260 --> 00:07:30.500
In your book you mentioned an example
when you didn't go on an excursion.

00:07:30.780 --> 00:07:36.060
There were a million examples when
you were deprived in your private life.

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:41.340
You had a very difficult path.

00:07:42.220 --> 00:07:46.140
How did you feel then and
what were your beginnings like?

00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:50.940
When did you realize that you would
dedicate your whole life to football?

00:07:54.620 --> 00:08:00.900
Giving up is an integral part of sports,
and an integral part of life.

00:08:01.100 --> 00:08:03.900
There are various types
of renunciation.

00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:08.380
If we're only going to talk about
that boyish renunciation,

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:14.300
that's excursions, staying outside
the building until 10 or 11 o'clock.

00:08:14.500 --> 00:08:17.820
And not go to sleep at 8 or 9
because you have practice tomorrow.

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:22.620
It's a sacrifice when it's winter
and you need an hour and a half

00:08:22.860 --> 00:08:26.420
drive to your practice and back.
You go to school,

00:08:26.620 --> 00:08:29.940
and there are times when
you think you won't succeed.

00:08:30.180 --> 00:08:34.180
No, that's abstinance,
a struggle with oneself.

00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:40.020
I need to say I grew up
in a normal, humble family.

00:08:40.260 --> 00:08:42.540
But I'm not complaining.

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:48.540
I think that helped me understand
some things quickly.

00:08:48.780 --> 00:08:52.980
I soon realized that football
would be my life.

00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:57.300
In the moments when
the sanctions for Serbia start

00:08:57.540 --> 00:09:00.340
and when all kinds of stupid
things happen all around us.

00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:03.940
As a child then, I did not understand
the suffering of my parents.

00:09:04.140 --> 00:09:08.900
What exhibitions and magic
they had to use to get me anything.

00:09:09.140 --> 00:09:13.140
At the same time they lost their jobs
when I made my debut for the first team

00:09:13.380 --> 00:09:16.370
at the age of 16 and a half
and got my first salary.

00:09:16.541 --> 00:09:19.323
Then I told my parents
that they will no longer work.

00:09:19.509 --> 00:09:25.510
Father worked in a tyre shop. And mother
chopped salad in a restaurant.

00:09:25.894 --> 00:09:31.659
When I got my first paycheck I told
them they won't be working anymore.

00:09:31.901 --> 00:09:36.026
So I had no choice between yes or no.
My only answer was yes.

00:09:36.420 --> 00:09:40.100
Now we will talk a bit about
your first club, FK Zemun.

00:09:40.420 --> 00:09:48.301
There is information that they
assessed in 1989 you had to talent.

00:09:48.960 --> 00:09:54.000
Is that true? Or was it by chance?
-It happened by chance.

00:09:54.343 --> 00:10:00.184
I went for a tryout.
Near the building I lived in.

00:10:01.027 --> 00:10:06.740
I watched FK Zemun
quite a few times.

00:10:07.860 --> 00:10:15.380
I grew up 1 km away
from the stadium.

00:10:17.060 --> 00:10:21.740
I went. After the first practice
they told me I was not talented.

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:26.140
The best thing I remember
was the tea after that practice.

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:28.860
It was sweet with plenty
of lemon. It was cold.

00:10:29.140 --> 00:10:32.420
A surprise soon followed since
they told me I was not talented,

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:36.100
that I could go to a smaller club
and come at later time.

00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:39.820
That was the assessment then.
I took it hard.

00:10:40.900 --> 00:10:47.340
But we didn't give up. -You were
around 8, 9 or 10 years old then?

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:52.340
If you mentioned 1989, I was about
11 years old. I was born in 1978.

00:10:52.580 --> 00:10:56.980
Those are sensitive years.
If I can't play for FK Zemun,

00:10:57.260 --> 00:11:00.340
it's better to change the sport.

00:11:00.700 --> 00:11:06.260
Mother was persistent, she worked
at INSA, a watch factory.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:12.260
There was a guy,
a goalkeeper at Teleoptik.

00:11:12.660 --> 00:11:19.300
His wife worked with my mother
and he said I should come for a tryout.

00:11:19.740 --> 00:11:25.620
After a month or two
of persuasion I went there.

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:29.820
Dragan Šipka was there.
He was the man who told me

00:11:30.060 --> 00:11:36.100
to bring two photos and
birth certificate for registration.

00:11:37.220 --> 00:11:43.300
After some eight months,
I transferred to Crvena Zvezda.

00:11:43.860 --> 00:11:49.660
Dragan Šipka noticed some things
better than his colleague.

00:11:50.860 --> 00:11:57.140
It was such a path and I accept it.
I didn't get mad at anyone.

00:11:57.660 --> 00:12:04.620
Later I met people who worked in
Zemun and we joked about that.

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:08.500
Also, Mateja Kežman
experienced a similar situation.

00:12:08.780 --> 00:12:12.620
We both left FK Zemun.
-You weren't famous.

00:12:12.900 --> 00:12:18.060
There were some
financial implications.

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:23.900
That would have been a good
situation for the club too.

00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:28.300
I want to thank everyone
because I was a little boy.

00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:31.380
I played for the cadets,
youngest categorie.

00:12:31.580 --> 00:12:34.860
Dragan Šipka put me in
the play whenever he could.

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:38.980
Then they started
talking about me.

00:12:40.380 --> 00:12:43.180
I transferred to Crvena Zvezda.

00:12:43.540 --> 00:12:49.140
Toma Milićević started organizing
friendly matches during the winter.

00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:54.340
Rumors started circulating
about me very quickly.

00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:57.940
Toma Milićević was the coach
of the Crvena Zvezda youngest.

00:12:58.180 --> 00:13:02.220
He also organized friendly matches
in the Crvena Zvezda gym,

00:13:02.540 --> 00:13:06.740
and it was located above my
previous office, where I worked

00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:11.420
as the head of the professional staff.
Above is the handball gym.

00:13:11.740 --> 00:13:17.100
﻿ He organized the two friendly matches,
in the handball gym above the office,

00:13:17.300 --> 00:13:20.940
as small-sided games to bring people
from Crvena Zvezda to see me play.

00:13:21.220 --> 00:13:24.580
That's how the story of them insisting
on me started. Some other clubs

00:13:24.820 --> 00:13:29.180
were also involved, which gave
my father a sense of importance.

00:13:29.380 --> 00:13:34.060
They were also offering my father
job positions in different cities

00:13:34.260 --> 00:13:39.980
so I could join their clubs, but
there was never a shadow of a doubt

00:13:40.260 --> 00:13:44.540
that I would go to Zvezda
if they called me.

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:48.362
I went to Zvezda and started
from the youngest team.

00:13:48.784 --> 00:13:51.042
I played for them in
Crvena Zvezda for two years,

00:13:51.196 --> 00:13:53.275
and that is how
my fast journey started.

00:13:58.300 --> 00:14:03.820
And that's how the story of your
professional career starts.

00:14:04.620 --> 00:14:09.380
You debuted at 16 in such a team.

00:14:09.660 --> 00:14:14.605
Two or three years prior, you were
picking up balls from the field

00:14:14.798 --> 00:14:18.293
and watching the generation of '91
players play, and suddenly,

00:14:18.517 --> 00:14:22.371
you were sharing a field with them.
-Yes. -How did that look like for you?

00:14:22.627 --> 00:14:26.238
Zvezda teaches you quickly
what kind of club it is, how big it is,

00:14:26.460 --> 00:14:29.332
and what it expects from you
in the future. There were probably

00:14:29.488 --> 00:14:33.180
more talented players in my generation
than me. Not probably, but there were

00:14:33.341 --> 00:14:38.155
100% more talented and better players
than me. However, my sacrifice and

00:14:38.311 --> 00:14:43.460
work ethic proved to be
something good in the long run.

00:14:46.260 --> 00:14:49.340
I spent four years in Zvezda
in the younger categories.

00:14:49.540 --> 00:14:55.300
When I was 16,5 years old,
Ljupko put me against OFK Beograd

00:14:55.500 --> 00:15:00.460
at the point in the game where
the score was 1-2. We were leading.

00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:04.340
It was a serious league at the time.
-And you were 16 years old.

00:15:04.540 --> 00:15:09.900
I was precisely 16,5 years old.
It was the 11th of February in 1995.

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:14.020
I was born on the
11th of September in 1978.

00:15:15.660 --> 00:15:19.580
And that's when everything started.
I like to say I was like a rocket ship

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:22.580
for three years. After those
three years, I left Zvezda.

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:25.700
A lot of things happened.
I had to grow up quickly.

00:15:25.940 --> 00:15:30.020
I had a phenomenal group of young men
around me. I had the opportunity to see

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:33.860
who was a good example and who wasn't.
The team protected me.

00:15:35.460 --> 00:15:42.900
I had amazing conditions become better.
Nenad Sakić is a part of my staff now.

00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:49.180
He joined Zvezda in 1994
and was like an older brother to me.

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:56.340
I'm sure I let them know what
kind of a person I am with my behavior.

00:15:56.510 --> 00:16:00.308
I had phenomenal teammates
who protected me

00:16:00.484 --> 00:16:04.131
and gave me the opportunity
to show my best self.

00:16:10.140 --> 00:16:16.340
That all happened from your 16th to your
19th year, a quick rise to fame.

00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:24.420
You get an offer from Lazio
of 25-24 million marks.

00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:30.580
I don't even know what that amount
would be today. -In that moment...

00:16:30.820 --> 00:16:36.260
That was unbelievable for you
as a 19-year-old at the time.

00:16:36.500 --> 00:16:40.900
If you divide that amount by half
and say 12-12,5 million euros,

00:16:41.140 --> 00:16:47.020
it doesn't sound so jawdropping. But at
that moment, 24-25 million marks were...

00:16:47.260 --> 00:16:50.500
What would the equivalent
of that today be? -I don't know...

00:16:50.740 --> 00:16:54.860
Maybe even 150 million. -I don't know.
Given those circumstances and where

00:16:55.100 --> 00:16:59.940
I was coming from, it was a huge sum of
money. It was such a huge sum of money

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:05.420
that a transfer had to be organized.
I remember landing in Rome for

00:17:05.700 --> 00:17:10.825
the first time for checkups with
a private airplane Cragnotti sent.

00:17:11.087 --> 00:17:15.607
Cragnotti said: "Bring me the kid so I
can see who I paid so much money for."

00:17:15.815 --> 00:17:18.615
He wanted to see me in person.
He never saw me because his scouts

00:17:18.964 --> 00:17:23.844
Sven-Göran Eriksson, Mancini and Siniša
were responsible for my arrival.

00:17:24.420 --> 00:17:29.500
He said: "Okay, okay, I trust you.
Just bring me the kid so I can meet him

00:17:29.700 --> 00:17:33.100
in person. To see what I gave
25 million marks for."

00:17:33.340 --> 00:17:37.100
That's how my story in Lazio,
the dream team, started. -Dream team...

00:17:37.300 --> 00:17:40.980
14 players were brought on that summer.
You didn't know who was paid more,

00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:46.900
had a better contract or was a bigger
star. But from the very beginning,

00:17:47.100 --> 00:17:50.180
good chemistry was established.
-You achieved great results. -Yes.

00:17:50.420 --> 00:17:53.180
That was all thanks to
Sven-Göran Eriksson.

00:17:53.420 --> 00:17:58.043
At that moment, he was the only man
that could lead that team. Nobody else.

00:17:58.229 --> 00:18:01.309
Trust me when I tell you, Trust me.
-Outstanding individuals:

00:18:01.820 --> 00:18:09.185
Nedved, Bokšić, Almeyda, Mancini,
Salas, you... -Conceicao. -Conceicao.

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:15.100
Verón joined us the following year.
In the same year, we also won a title.

00:18:15.380 --> 00:18:21.100
Siniša and Couto were also brought in
the first year during the summer.

00:18:21.700 --> 00:18:26.020
We won the Cup Winners' Cup, which was
also the last ever Cup Winners' Cup.

00:18:26.260 --> 00:18:29.500
That was in 1999? -Yes, in 1999.
It was the 98/99 season.

00:18:29.740 --> 00:18:35.020
And that was the last one like that?
-Yes. The last Cup Winners' Cup

00:18:35.260 --> 00:18:43.300
was in 1999. We won against Mallorca.
I was almost 20 years old then.

00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:51.100
In 1999, I had just turned 20
and was already on the podium.

00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:56.580
I was dreaming about it and watching it
for a long time. Everything took off

00:18:56.940 --> 00:19:00.340
very quickly. The summer Super Cup
was against Manchester United.

00:19:00.540 --> 00:19:03.860
That kind of game was something I
watched, for instance, when they won

00:19:04.100 --> 00:19:06.900
against Bayern with two goals
in the last four minutes.

00:19:07.180 --> 00:19:14.020
To play against guys like Dwight Yorke,
David Beckham, Neville, Paul Scholes,

00:19:14.300 --> 00:19:17.020
and the whole team... -That's a big
deal. -It's a big deal indeed.

00:19:17.900 --> 00:19:21.300
Suddenly, you're playing against all of
them when you were watching them

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:25.460
just a year ago and dreaming of sharing
a field. You just have to respect that.

00:19:25.700 --> 00:19:29.620
It deserves a lot of respect. You pinch
yourself to realize where you are now.

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:33.820
You understand that you want to stay
there, at that level. That is what

00:19:34.020 --> 00:19:39.060
we were talking about. That is when you
start putting in the actual effort.

00:19:39.580 --> 00:19:42.260
That is when you start putting in the
actual effort. -The pressure,

00:19:42.460 --> 00:19:45.140
expectations, invested money... -Yes,
the invested money... There's pressure.

00:19:45.340 --> 00:19:48.820
You want to always be on the top.

00:19:49.420 --> 00:19:52.340
You're just proving yourself from one
season to the next. It's nothing to

00:19:52.580 --> 00:19:55.500
a club to pay 15-30 million to bring
someone new in to replace you.

00:19:55.740 --> 00:19:59.500
So that makes keeping your place
in the team much harder.

00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:04.260
I managed to do that for almost 6 years
in Lazio and almost 10 years in Inter.

00:20:04.460 --> 00:20:09.180
I changed only two clubs. I consider
myself to be a very persistent man.

00:20:11.140 --> 00:20:14.060
I played every single year.

00:20:14.300 --> 00:20:17.540
I had to pause in 1999/2000
because I was a foreigner.

00:20:17.780 --> 00:20:21.020
I was the fourth "extracomunitario"
or someone from outside of the EU.

00:20:21.260 --> 00:20:26.340
At that time, the bombarding happened,
and I wasn't thinking about football.

00:20:26.502 --> 00:20:29.622
Football was on my...
-Last on your list. -Last on my list.

00:20:29.800 --> 00:20:32.400
For six months,
I was on some sort of a break.

00:20:32.555 --> 00:20:37.915
I was always playing with every coach
before and after that period.

00:20:43.060 --> 00:20:47.460
We are moving on.
Lazio won the double crown,

00:20:49.900 --> 00:20:55.500
which was the second biggest success for
the club. However, the downfall began.

00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:59.340
There were financial issues, and the
atmosphere started to wither down.

00:20:59.580 --> 00:21:03.380
There was a feeling in the air that
Lazio was experiencing a downfall.

00:21:03.620 --> 00:21:08.140
That's when you changed clubs
and moved to Inter Milano,

00:21:08.340 --> 00:21:11.820
but many clubs showed interest.
In the midst of all of that,

00:21:12.060 --> 00:21:16.980
some complications arose. I would like
to ask you to explain that situation.

00:21:17.820 --> 00:21:23.180
I assume those days were traumatic.
-It wasn't traumatic,

00:21:23.980 --> 00:21:28.220
but there were a lot of big challenges.
I felt sorry for Lazio because,

00:21:28.460 --> 00:21:32.940
at the time, it was a phenomenal
"piazza" (place) to live and play in.

00:21:33.420 --> 00:21:39.620
Everything was over the top. We had the
best of the best regarding conditions

00:21:39.860 --> 00:21:43.300
and the sports center, which at the time
looked like a space shuttle.

00:21:43.500 --> 00:21:46.180
The mode of travel,
the way of playing,

00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:49.940
and the way everything
functioned were phenomenal.

00:21:50.180 --> 00:21:54.620
I'm sure nobody thought about something
like that having an end date.

00:21:54.980 --> 00:22:00.020
Sadly, the end did come. There were some
financial issues followed by multiple

00:22:00.260 --> 00:22:03.460
departures from the team
and a change of club policies.

00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:10.356
Then, the final year of my
contract came, and, as you said,

00:22:11.388 --> 00:22:16.900
many clubs reached out with solid
offers. -Juventus was close, right?

00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:23.500
Yes, Juventus was close. It was close.
It was very close. It almost happened.

00:22:23.740 --> 00:22:25.700
We don't have to go into details.
-We don't have to go into details.

00:22:25.900 --> 00:22:27.940
We won't. -I can't go into details.

00:22:28.820 --> 00:22:38.589
I had a gut feeling. Inter reached out,
too, amongst many other Italian clubs.

00:22:41.620 --> 00:22:47.420
I spoke with Mancini. That talk wasn't
the deciding factor since I was already

00:22:47.700 --> 00:22:51.620
drawn to Inter, but he said,
"I have a feeling that if you go there,

00:22:51.900 --> 00:22:57.020
you will write history in golden
letters." -Mancini said that?

00:22:57.260 --> 00:23:02.780
Yes, Mancini. And then, of course,
I might have heard some whispers

00:23:03.020 --> 00:23:09.380
that he might also come to Inter that
summer. So, our paths crossed again

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:17.012
"coincidentally", if anything in life
can be called a coincidence.

00:23:18.580 --> 00:23:20.380
We started writing history.

00:23:20.620 --> 00:23:25.300
I changed clubs. There was a lot of back
and forth. They submitted the contract

00:23:25.500 --> 00:23:28.060
at the last minute on the last day
of the transition period.

00:23:28.300 --> 00:23:31.620
The driver who delivered the contract
and was later with me in the club

00:23:31.860 --> 00:23:35.300
for 10 years said that that drive
from the club to the Association

00:23:35.540 --> 00:23:39.340
was the hardest one because he was on
the reserve and there were only

00:23:39.540 --> 00:23:43.940
15 minutes until the doors closed. He
said that if he didn't make it on time,

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:48.300
no Inter fan would forgive him for that.
He made it at the last minute

00:23:48.540 --> 00:23:53.780
and submitted the contract.
I was preparing for a game with Lazio,

00:23:54.020 --> 00:23:58.220
and my last day was a Saturday,
which was also the last day of

00:23:58.420 --> 00:24:01.380
the transition period with Zaccheroni.
He is a phenomenal coach and a person

00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:06.380
with whom I'm still keeping in touch.
I owe him a great deal of gratitude.

00:24:07.020 --> 00:24:09.420
I was getting ready to go to
Siena on that Saturday.

00:24:09.660 --> 00:24:13.260
He asked if I could play right away
and said of course. The very next day,

00:24:13.460 --> 00:24:16.540
I was playing for Inter.
I had my baptism by fire.

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.655
Taking a first step at San Siro
is such a special feeling.

00:24:21.740 --> 00:24:26.020
I think it's a tough stadium, trust me.
-Is it tough when Milan or Inter plays?

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:33.446
No... San Siro, whether from Milan or
Inter, ate up players much better than

00:24:33.642 --> 00:24:38.460
I ever was. That pressure, ambient,
demanding fans... That kind of pressure

00:24:40.331 --> 00:24:47.404
ate up Seedrof and Pirlo in Inter.
They didn't succeed then,

00:24:48.280 --> 00:24:53.520
but they did in Milan. Their moments
in San Siro weren't the best.

00:24:55.980 --> 00:25:00.500
That first match knocked down all
barriers between San Siro and me.

00:25:00.740 --> 00:25:03.540
I knew what it meant.
It's the same thing with Milan Scala.

00:25:03.780 --> 00:25:07.860
To play in Milan in that stadium is
a spectacle. I was really enjoying it.

00:25:09.620 --> 00:25:13.820
I got rid of the barriers. We won
and slowly reached our first goal,

00:25:14.180 --> 00:25:18.900
to enter the first four teams.
I came in when we were in the 7th place.

00:25:19.460 --> 00:25:22.020
We got to the first four teams
and had the qualifications...

00:25:22.260 --> 00:25:25.580
For the Champions League? -We got
to the qualifications and into the last,

00:25:25.820 --> 00:25:29.500
or second to last round. Adriano
also joined Inter after being

00:25:29.740 --> 00:25:33.620
a loan player for Parma, so the two of
us started playing in the winter.

00:25:33.727 --> 00:25:37.248
We managed to climb from the 7th to the
4th place. Mancini also came, and we

00:25:37.353 --> 00:25:40.357
entered the Champions League by beating
Basel. And that's how it starts.

00:25:40.439 --> 00:25:43.232
That's how the era of Mancini started,
and afterward of José.

00:25:48.380 --> 00:25:52.020
Can I just circle back for a moment?
-Yes, of course. -Álvaro Recoba

00:25:53.140 --> 00:25:57.580
and that one penalty kick. Can we
talk a bit about that? Is that true?

00:25:57.820 --> 00:26:00.820
Yes, it's true.
I don't like penalties.

00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:04.660
Not because I'm afraid
of taking the shot,

00:26:05.140 --> 00:26:08.380
but because if I miss,
the disappointment will be much greater

00:26:08.580 --> 00:26:13.260
than the joy of scoring the goal.
But I didn’t hide.

00:26:13.460 --> 00:26:17.260
I took shots even when there were
penalties after 90 or 120 minutes.

00:26:17.900 --> 00:26:19.660
Whenever it was necessary.

00:26:19.940 --> 00:26:22.780
He came when it was 3-0
and gave me the ball.

00:26:23.340 --> 00:26:25.940
I told him, if you're the one
who's going to take the penalty

00:26:26.180 --> 00:26:30.060
when it's 0-0 and the 90th minute,
you'll be the one to take it

00:26:30.260 --> 00:26:34.500
when it's 3-0 and the 85th minute.
That’s how I see things.

00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:37.500
It's easy to take a penalty at 3-0.
No. In my opinion,

00:26:37.700 --> 00:26:41.340
the one who should always take it
is the one who will take the shot

00:26:41.540 --> 00:26:47.740
in the 90th minute at 0-0, and a goal
we need to win the trophy. -I agree.

00:26:47.980 --> 00:26:51.020
That same person shoots
at 5-0 and at 0-0.

00:26:51.220 --> 00:26:56.620
I said, Chino, your left foot
is magical. He scored, 4-0.

00:26:57.540 --> 00:27:00.453
After that, I started scoring
goals in my own way.

00:27:00.759 --> 00:27:03.199
Let's go back to your way.

00:27:03.700 --> 00:27:07.780
That shot of yours
is really rare to see.

00:27:08.580 --> 00:27:15.100
You had a top-notch shot. It seems to me
that you developed it over time.

00:27:15.340 --> 00:27:20.300
It became more dangerous and
you were scoring from greater distances.

00:27:20.580 --> 00:27:25.180
In important matches. I would
mention the derby against Milan,

00:27:25.380 --> 00:27:28.860
which was probably the most important
during your time at Inter.

00:27:29.100 --> 00:27:32.340
You scored 3-4 of the most important
goals in 12 matches. -Yes.

00:27:32.580 --> 00:27:35.140
How did that come about?

00:27:35.740 --> 00:27:40.420
All your attempts, not just the goals,
over time, along with your status,

00:27:40.660 --> 00:27:43.180
did that contribute to
the quality of your shot?

00:27:43.460 --> 00:27:48.020
Definitely. From this point of view,
preparation is 80% of the shot.

00:27:48.260 --> 00:27:51.020
I had excellent preparation.

00:27:51.420 --> 00:27:57.140
Ball reception, the distance at reception,
body positioning that shields the ball.

00:27:57.340 --> 00:27:59.980
There's an anecdote.
As a kid, I grew a lot,

00:28:00.220 --> 00:28:06.540
and I already had a size 43-44 foot
as a young cadet.

00:28:06.980 --> 00:28:10.860
We trained indoors with
Zvezda during winter.

00:28:11.180 --> 00:28:16.340
Šeki was there, playing football
with his friends.

00:28:16.660 --> 00:28:23.460
He saw my problem, that I couldn’t
kick properly because of my large feet.

00:28:24.037 --> 00:28:29.361
He showed me how to kick
with the outside of my foot,

00:28:29.781 --> 00:28:35.400
so I wouldn’t scrape the ground.
To switch to the outside.

00:28:36.522 --> 00:28:41.522
I liked that,
and I started doing it.

00:28:42.300 --> 00:28:49.700
Preparation for that is 80% of the job.
My preparation was phenomenal.

00:28:49.940 --> 00:28:57.020
I always liked to "wrap it" a bit
with the outside, to curve it away.

00:28:57.540 --> 00:29:04.541
I scored a lot of goals
because of the shot preparation.

00:29:06.533 --> 00:29:11.700
Body positioning is important,
the standing leg, the hip rotation.

00:29:11.880 --> 00:29:16.833
When you shoot, how you follow
the ball with your body.

00:29:21.740 --> 00:29:24.660
Try to imagine the situation
and finish this.

00:29:24.940 --> 00:29:28.260
Cambiaso on the left side.
I'm talking about Schalke.

00:29:28.500 --> 00:29:32.700
A long ball goes toward Eto'o...
-Milito. -Milito.

00:29:32.940 --> 00:29:37.460
The goalkeeper comes out,
almost 30-40 meters.

00:29:38.060 --> 00:29:43.380
Almost from the center.
That wasn’t the first time for me.

00:29:43.660 --> 00:29:46.220
In the younger categories,
I scored similar goals.

00:29:46.460 --> 00:29:50.100
The goalkeeper kicks the ball and
I return it immediately from the circle.

00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:52.780
Back then, we were smaller.
He would come to the 16-meter line.

00:29:53.020 --> 00:29:55.420
He kicks it so the ball
lands at midfield.

00:29:55.660 --> 00:29:58.220
As the ball comes to me,
I return it immediately.

00:29:58.460 --> 00:30:02.060
That was a volley, it went like this.
-Some say it's a beautiful goal.

00:30:02.300 --> 00:30:05.820
I say it's a crazy goal.
They ask when I decided.

00:30:06.100 --> 00:30:10.140
When I saw it coming toward me,
I knew what I would do.

00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:16.460
I love that shot, the coordination
of the volley, the body positioning...

00:30:18.540 --> 00:30:20.860
Everything was in place there.

00:30:21.140 --> 00:30:25.220
I hit few crossbars and I scored
some goals from the halfway line.

00:30:25.460 --> 00:30:29.140
After that, I scored another goal
from midfield against Genoa.

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:32.780
Maybe even harder than this one.

00:30:33.020 --> 00:30:37.580
This one was beautiful, exactly
the way I like to curve the ball.

00:30:38.060 --> 00:30:42.740
For it to go in but not touch
the ground before the line.

00:30:42.980 --> 00:30:47.620
Yes, it didn’t touch the ground.
-A crazy goal,

00:30:48.140 --> 00:30:52.220
but it requires coordination.
That’s what we were talking about.

00:30:52.460 --> 00:30:55.500
Body positioning and coordination
are 80% of the shot.

00:30:55.740 --> 00:31:00.340
Someone might have a stronger shot,
but coordination is key for precision.

00:31:00.540 --> 00:31:02.900
To score a goal,
you have to hit the target.

00:31:04.340 --> 00:31:08.620
The year is 2010.
The golden age of Inter.

00:31:09.020 --> 00:31:18.896
2009/2010, Mourinho, triple crown.
The icing on the career for most of you.

00:31:20.219 --> 00:31:24.279
The last train, not icing.
I agree with you.

00:31:25.685 --> 00:31:28.677
For most players. -For 90%.

00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:36.340
If we start listing the starting eleven.
Materazzi and I came into the game.

00:31:36.540 --> 00:31:40.620
We were 32 and 35 years old.
Zanetti was 36, Cambiasso 31,

00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:46.620
Maicon 28-29, Wesley 30,
Milito 31. Eto'o 32,

00:31:46.980 --> 00:31:49.780
Walter Samuel... -Yes, him.

00:31:50.020 --> 00:31:55.260
Over 90% of the players
were older than 30 years.

00:31:55.500 --> 00:31:58.540
We knew it was the end.

00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:06.220
During the group stage,
we barely made it through in Kiev,

00:32:06.460 --> 00:32:10.180
but when you watch the match,
it doesn’t seem so.

00:32:10.380 --> 00:32:13.380
We scored the goals in
the 89th and 94th minutes.

00:32:13.580 --> 00:32:16.620
That was already 50%
of the Champions League won.

00:32:16.820 --> 00:32:20.260
If we hadn’t won against
Rebrov and Shevchenko in offense,

00:32:20.500 --> 00:32:24.060
we wouldn’t have made it
through the group stage.

00:32:24.300 --> 00:32:27.540
You lost away to Barcelona,
and at home it was a draw.

00:32:27.820 --> 00:32:33.260
We needed to win that to secure
the last match against Rubin Kazan.

00:32:36.380 --> 00:32:42.820
In Kiev, we were losing at halftime.
Jose did things his way.

00:32:43.260 --> 00:32:46.780
He set us up
for the second half.

00:32:46.980 --> 00:32:50.780
From the start to the end,
we progressed, progressed.

00:32:50.940 --> 00:32:56.766
It paid off. It was incredible.
89th and 93rd minute, you advance.

00:32:56.971 --> 00:32:59.251
After that, 3-0 Rubin Kazan.

00:32:59.980 --> 00:33:06.100
That was a mature team,
they had no problems in the locker room.

00:33:06.420 --> 00:33:11.900
We didn’t need a director or Moratti
to come in. God forbid Moratti came.

00:33:12.220 --> 00:33:19.100
For us to allow the famous
Massimo Moratti to say something to us.

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:28.180
Never? -No. He’s a gentleman who was
in the wrong era of football management.

00:33:28.420 --> 00:33:33.180
He is so kind,
such a great gentleman.

00:33:33.460 --> 00:33:36.740
I didn’t see him in that world,
but he loves Inter.

00:33:36.940 --> 00:33:43.460
He says he's in love with Inter
like someone with the wrong woman.

00:33:43.700 --> 00:33:51.100
You love her, but she tortures you
in every possible way.

00:33:51.300 --> 00:33:56.420
But you have to know, when 80 thousand
people are insulting you, look up.

00:33:56.620 --> 00:33:58.940
There’s one man who adores you.

00:33:59.580 --> 00:34:03.460
That’s where it all begins and ends
when Massimo Moratti is mentioned.

00:34:03.660 --> 00:34:10.980
He embodies nobility. Not one
of his words was out of context.

00:34:11.220 --> 00:34:18.180
When you have such a president,
we need to act like nervous fools.

00:34:18.420 --> 00:34:22.740
There was so much ego in
the locker room you could export it.

00:34:22.980 --> 00:34:24.940
There were tons of egos.

00:34:25.061 --> 00:34:27.741
All that ego was directed
toward the success of Inter.

00:34:27.895 --> 00:34:33.652
We all felt that this man and
this crowd deserved such a year.

00:34:39.100 --> 00:34:41.580
It doesn’t matter anymore
if someone plays, doesn’t play,

00:34:41.780 --> 00:34:43.620
if you’re angry or not.

00:34:43.860 --> 00:34:45.700
In that moment, the first minute
is like the 90th,

00:34:45.900 --> 00:34:49.460
and the 90th is like the first.
All together, zero problems.

00:34:49.700 --> 00:34:53.060
If there were any, we dealt
with them behind closed doors.

00:34:53.300 --> 00:34:55.020
We came out even
better and stronger.

00:34:55.260 --> 00:34:59.620
We were adults. There were 25
players, and we had 60 kids.

00:35:00.820 --> 00:35:07.014
Together we had 50-60 kids.
One had three, another four...

00:35:08.460 --> 00:35:11.740
Like a family. -Everyone has kids,
and we need to act up

00:35:11.980 --> 00:35:16.039
or prove ourselves. To whom?
Just to ourselves,

00:35:16.391 --> 00:35:22.164
to prove that we can do it.
The atmosphere after that was...

00:35:23.061 --> 00:35:30.846
The next 20% was Chelsea.
It was the round of 16.

00:35:31.460 --> 00:35:37.340
Chelsea with Ancelotti and that team.
Drogba, F. Lampard, A. Cole,

00:35:38.980 --> 00:35:43.820
Terry, Peter Cech.
A serious team.

00:35:44.260 --> 00:35:48.900
We beat them 2:1, 0:1 in
a monstrous match in London.

00:35:50.580 --> 00:35:54.980
Did you lose? -We won 0:1.
Chelsea-Inter 0:1.

00:35:55.660 --> 00:35:59.260
The goal was scored by Eto'o
in the 81st or 82nd minute.

00:35:59.540 --> 00:36:06.140
That was the mastermind by José Mourinho
and all of us who played.

00:36:07.260 --> 00:36:11.780
In the draw, we were lucky.
CSKA, with due respect.

00:36:12.060 --> 00:36:18.580
After Barcelona. -After that,
we struggled. 1:0 at home.

00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:25.340
I know we won there,
artificial turf, it was cold,

00:36:25.580 --> 00:36:32.580
Sneijder, goalkeeper's mistake.
After that, the semifinals, Barcelona.

00:36:34.820 --> 00:36:39.860
Dream team, Pep Guardiola...
-Messi... -Messi is the best, Ibra.

00:36:40.580 --> 00:36:42.700
Who else was there?
Xavi, Iniesta...

00:36:42.900 --> 00:36:45.340
They were all top-notch
from that generation.

00:36:45.660 --> 00:36:48.260
Dani Alves, I don’t know
who was on the left.

00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:54.180
Puyol, Pique. The best
Barcelona team that ever played.

00:36:55.220 --> 00:36:56.740
You know...

00:36:59.260 --> 00:37:02.140
You played in
the group stage that year...

00:37:02.380 --> 00:37:04.980
In the group stage
we didn’t have much saying.

00:37:05.220 --> 00:37:09.660
Then comes the semifinals.
-Semifinals. You know how it is?

00:37:10.620 --> 00:37:13.740
You can’t have it twice.
You don’t accept that.

00:37:14.060 --> 00:37:18.620
The pressure was on them and on us.
I think it was more on them.

00:37:18.860 --> 00:37:26.260
You could feel it. In the first match,
the atmosphere was crazy. Unreal.

00:37:28.540 --> 00:37:33.820
We were the first team to manage
to turn around Barcelona at San Siro.

00:37:34.100 --> 00:37:39.860
It would usually be 0:2, 0:3, or 0:4.
We managed to turn that around

00:37:40.580 --> 00:37:44.420
and get to 3:1. -3:1.
-We turned the match around

00:37:44.700 --> 00:37:48.700
and took every chance
we had to punish them.

00:37:48.940 --> 00:37:53.700
A volcano erupted in Finland,
stopping air traffic.

00:37:53.940 --> 00:37:57.140
They traveled by bus.
They traveled for 2-3 days.

00:37:57.380 --> 00:38:01.420
They slept everywhere
until they reached Milan.

00:38:01.820 --> 00:38:05.820
All of that can and may not
affect the final result.

00:38:06.140 --> 00:38:09.660
Then comes the drama in Barcelona.

00:38:09.980 --> 00:38:14.500
I don’t believe I’ll experience
longer 100 minutes.

00:38:14.700 --> 00:38:19.500
That’s when you closed up.
The formation was extremely defensive.

00:38:19.740 --> 00:38:24.020
We had offensive players,
but we played defensively.

00:38:25.060 --> 00:38:29.700
Milito, Eto'o, Pandev, Sneijder played.
We were all like one.

00:38:30.220 --> 00:38:36.580
We had offensive players, but the strength
of Barcelona at that moment...

00:38:36.900 --> 00:38:40.180
One full-back was Eto'o,
and Pandev was the other.

00:38:40.420 --> 00:38:44.260
That’s what I’m talking about
the locker room with tons of egos,

00:38:44.540 --> 00:38:48.540
but Samuel played left-back
with his weaker foot,

00:38:48.740 --> 00:38:52.900
while Goran Pandev played
right-back with his weaker foot.

00:38:53.180 --> 00:38:58.420
From corner flag to corner flag. -Muntari
came in because Pandev got injured.

00:38:58.620 --> 00:39:03.460
Muntari was the sixth,
because we had six in the line.

00:39:05.260 --> 00:39:08.740
It was a serious barricade.
But I agree with José.

00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:13.598
I need to be brave and die
or I’ll struggle and pass through.

00:39:14.214 --> 00:39:16.635
﻿I think you should work hard.

00:39:16.893 --> 00:39:21.190
You can't fight a stronger one,
but you can hit and run.

00:39:21.786 --> 00:39:24.706
You find a way to punish
your opponent.

00:39:25.540 --> 00:39:29.260
We defended ourselves.
Julio Cesar had two saves,

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:33.740
in my opinion,
are the saves of his career.

00:39:34.060 --> 00:39:38.700
In the first half, he saves
Messi's ball with his fingernails.

00:39:38.980 --> 00:39:42.198
To Messi who scored
countless such goals.

00:39:42.287 --> 00:39:44.327
We're advancing to the finals...

00:39:44.668 --> 00:39:47.963
There is an anecdote, so if
you are interested, I will tell you.

00:39:48.140 --> 00:39:50.620
But not in front of the cameras?
-I can, I can.

00:39:50.940 --> 00:39:52.820
Tell me, please, if you can.

00:39:56.980 --> 00:40:00.900
The finals comes up. We have
already won the Italian Cup.

00:40:01.940 --> 00:40:05.420
We are getting closer
to the Scudetto title

00:40:08.300 --> 00:40:10.781
and we are already in the finals
of the Champions League.

00:40:10.903 --> 00:40:13.143
We will play the final
match with Bayern.

00:40:14.260 --> 00:40:18.420
Materazzi, Kivu, Wesley Sneijder
and I are at dinner with our wives,

00:40:19.020 --> 00:40:21.980
and Joze went with his staff
to watch the cup final

00:40:22.180 --> 00:40:25.740
at the Olympic Stadium in Berlin.

00:40:26.020 --> 00:40:29.580
Bayern played,
but I don't know against whom.

00:40:30.300 --> 00:40:34.220
Marco corresponds with Jose.
He asks how he is and the like...

00:40:34.460 --> 00:40:36.300
And Materazzi adds:
"Ask him how my stadium is?

00:40:36.540 --> 00:40:40.620
Because Marko lifted the world champion
trophy with the Italian national team

00:40:40.860 --> 00:40:44.300
at that Olympic stadium in Berlin.
The atmosphere was phenomenal then.

00:40:44.500 --> 00:40:47.940
Materazzi then asked him
what our opponents were like.

00:40:48.140 --> 00:40:51.220
And Jose answers:
"We will win 2:0.

00:40:52.900 --> 00:40:56.820
We played the final game on May 22.

00:40:57.380 --> 00:41:03.100
If you check in the archives
when the German cup final was,

00:41:03.340 --> 00:41:07.924
that's the date, and Jose is
more than two weeks earlier

00:41:08.495 --> 00:41:10.860
said that we will win 2:0.

00:41:13.100 --> 00:41:16.860
The eight of us can testify
to that.  Us and our wives.

00:41:17.100 --> 00:41:20.140
That's how it happened.
-That's how it happened, yes.

00:41:20.380 --> 00:41:22.340
In nice warm Madrid.

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:25.460
To play in Madrid
and achieve such success

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:28.980
in a stadium that has its own history,
in front of a huge number of fans

00:41:29.260 --> 00:41:33.100
who create an incredible
atmosphere, means a lot.

00:41:33.340 --> 00:41:37.340
When we suffered,
we knew why we were suffering.

00:41:37.780 --> 00:41:41.380
When we punished,
we punished good.

00:41:41.580 --> 00:41:43.940
We all gave more
than we should have.

00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:46.380
Both against Bayern
and against Barca,

00:41:46.660 --> 00:41:50.300
more than 100% effort
should have been given.

00:41:50.540 --> 00:41:53.220
We all had to concentrate,
ignore our egos and be normal,

00:41:53.500 --> 00:41:57.260
be modest and "smaller
than a poppy seed".

00:41:58.060 --> 00:42:00.718
Jose managed to get
the most out of all of us.

00:42:01.266 --> 00:42:05.835
I thought I had given everything
to football, but he managed,

00:42:06.152 --> 00:42:10.872
to pull out another 20 or 30%
of my strength and I repeat this often.

00:42:11.018 --> 00:42:14.574
He instilled in me a desire to never
give up to show what I'm here for.

00:42:14.790 --> 00:42:16.839
We all gave that 20% more.

00:42:17.059 --> 00:42:20.089
When a group of guys give
20% more strenght each,

00:42:20.293 --> 00:42:24.573
the result is a triple crown and
you remain inscribed somewhere.

00:42:25.660 --> 00:42:28.996
in golden letters and close the circle.
Just like I told you before.

00:42:29.114 --> 00:42:34.074
That's why you come to Inter and work
and defend those colors for 10 years.

00:42:34.192 --> 00:42:35.121
The reason is respect.

00:42:40.580 --> 00:42:43.260
Until 2010. everything was perfect.

00:42:43.580 --> 00:42:52.180
It's an impressive career
from Zvezda until 2010 or 2011.

00:42:52.420 --> 00:42:57.900
There were no big problems,
and then Rafael Benitez came,

00:42:58.140 --> 00:43:02.300
about whom I even heard stories,
including Pandev,

00:43:02.500 --> 00:43:05.780
that he was not a fan of players
from our region.

00:43:05.980 --> 00:43:12.940
You had a pretty bad relationship
because of that. Is that true?

00:43:13.180 --> 00:43:21.860
Are these some journalistic topics,
a half-truth or was it really like that.

00:43:22.100 --> 00:43:25.700
Now that I'm doing this job,
I can understand some things better.

00:43:25.900 --> 00:43:28.365
I am much older
and more experienced...

00:43:29.305 --> 00:43:32.545
When Jose left,
he left a huge void,

00:43:33.020 --> 00:43:38.780
and Benitez came with his own ideas,
which I somewhat understand.

00:43:39.060 --> 00:43:44.700
A similar thing happened to me when
I came to Ferencvaros as a new coach.

00:43:44.940 --> 00:43:48.781
When I arrived, I had my ideas,
my own way, which can automatically

00:43:48.949 --> 00:43:52.189
lead to opposition,
resistance and rejection.

00:43:53.780 --> 00:43:56.980
But it's a process
you have to go through.

00:43:57.180 --> 00:43:59.380
You can't come with a deflated ball,
inflate it and say:

00:43:59.620 --> 00:44:01.940
"Now I will show you
how to play football."

00:44:02.980 --> 00:44:09.780
We didn't play badly under Benitez,
although there were disagreements.

00:44:12.180 --> 00:44:20.780
It all ended with winning
the club world championship.

00:44:21.100 --> 00:44:25.460
After that, president Moratti
visited us and decided

00:44:25.700 --> 00:44:28.340
to change that after only
6 months of cooperation.

00:44:28.660 --> 00:44:32.100
I would not go into details,
nor attach any special importance to it.

00:44:32.340 --> 00:44:34.420
I am glad that we closed
that cycle by winning

00:44:34.620 --> 00:44:36.660
the Club World Cup,

00:44:37.660 --> 00:44:41.980
despite the fact that we
had a pretty bad relationship.

00:44:42.260 --> 00:44:46.180
But from this point of view
it is no big deal.

00:44:46.980 --> 00:44:50.940
When you are a player you
can only see some things.

00:44:51.180 --> 00:44:53.620
You only see what's on stage.

00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:59.340
And when you are a coach,
you can see what is on stage

00:44:59.780 --> 00:45:03.660
and what is behind the stage
and what is behind the curtain.

00:45:03.860 --> 00:45:08.669
You can see a lot, and as a player
you only see that in front of you.

00:45:09.193 --> 00:45:15.220
I must admit that our relationship
with him wasn't good either.

00:45:15.620 --> 00:45:21.580
Certainly not. When he encountered
some resistance, and he was a coach

00:45:21.940 --> 00:45:27.774
who has his own credits, his own
greatness, and he won many cups,

00:45:28.196 --> 00:45:30.899
he probably showed us
who's in charge.

00:45:31.231 --> 00:45:33.969
From this perspective,
I see it that way.

00:45:34.283 --> 00:45:38.402
I can only say that we did not
understand each other.

00:45:38.839 --> 00:45:44.691
After that everything was different.
We started to disperse and leave.

00:45:45.211 --> 00:45:49.535
Everyone sought their
luck in some other clubs.

00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:52.060
I stayed there until the end.

00:45:52.300 --> 00:45:55.740
I also had a tendon injury, which
unfortunately I operated twice.

00:45:55.980 --> 00:45:59.220
When I returned,
I thought this is it, now I will play,

00:45:59.406 --> 00:46:01.896
but then a coach came
who hadn't even notice me.

00:46:02.070 --> 00:46:04.710
It was great for me. I decided
to use the extra days of rest,

00:46:04.927 --> 00:46:07.927
and came to Moratti.  We sat down,
drank coffee, lit a cigar.

00:46:08.065 --> 00:46:10.065
I always had coffee with him
and smoked,

00:46:10.203 --> 00:46:12.216
now I can say that,
because I don't play.

00:46:12.383 --> 00:46:14.423
He also gave me a gold coin.

00:46:17.020 --> 00:46:25.100
We chatted often, as I extended
the contract three times

00:46:25.580 --> 00:46:30.140
sitting with him
over coffee and a cigar.

00:46:30.420 --> 00:46:33.220
You have also terminated
the contract. -That's right.

00:46:33.500 --> 00:46:37.420
I thanked him, because
he was a real gentleman.

00:46:38.180 --> 00:46:44.380
I could go to Fiorentina
at that moment,

00:46:44.940 --> 00:46:50.940
because they were giving me
a contract for two years.

00:46:51.340 --> 00:46:55.500
I asked for some time to think,
because I always said

00:46:55.780 --> 00:46:59.140
that I would end my career
with Inter or Milan.

00:46:59.380 --> 00:47:03.420
I could go on, but I like to
joke and say that I tasted

00:47:03.660 --> 00:47:07.820
the sea in July and it was
just as salty as it was in June.

00:47:08.060 --> 00:47:12.580
I liked that, so I decided
to say goodbye.

00:47:13.013 --> 00:47:16.373
The fact that the sea is always equally
salty helped you make a decision.

00:47:16.620 --> 00:47:20.580
Yes, we always went to the sea
in June when it was a little cooler.

00:47:20.780 --> 00:47:24.950
Since it was equally salty,
I liked that.

00:47:25.348 --> 00:47:29.707
Honestly, I wasn't
ready to leave football.

00:47:30.700 --> 00:47:36.140
Although after 20 years
of intense work and adrenaline,

00:47:36.380 --> 00:47:43.820
the first year was quite difficult,
quite strong, emotionally and mentally.

00:47:44.460 --> 00:47:47.500
You just don't know
where the fence is.

00:47:47.740 --> 00:47:51.100
You would hold on,
but you don't know where it is.

00:47:51.340 --> 00:47:54.340
You feel a little dizzy and if you
haven't prepared the airbag,

00:47:54.580 --> 00:47:57.780
you will lose the ground
under your feet.

00:47:57.980 --> 00:48:00.820
It wasn't easy the first year,
but slowly after that

00:48:00.950 --> 00:48:02.966
you catch the rhythm and move on.

00:48:07.900 --> 00:48:11.500
Now we are moving from
the club career to national team.

00:48:11.740 --> 00:48:14.340
You had great teammates
in the national team,

00:48:14.580 --> 00:48:19.620
but not the results that, in my opinion,
would match that level.

00:48:20.140 --> 00:48:25.180
What do you think prevented
you from achieving more?

00:48:25.980 --> 00:48:29.980
You must have had many
guests in this series

00:48:30.220 --> 00:48:35.700
who played for
the Serbian national team.

00:48:35.900 --> 00:48:38.940
I don't believe that either
of us will say anything bad

00:48:39.220 --> 00:48:42.620
or that either of
us will say anything else.

00:48:42.900 --> 00:48:45.740
I just feel sorry about '98.

00:48:46.003 --> 00:48:48.123
That year I joined
that national team and played

00:48:48.355 --> 00:48:50.635
until 2010, but because of that
my heart hurts even today.

00:48:50.915 --> 00:48:53.315
You were very close then.
-Of course we are.

00:48:53.586 --> 00:48:59.506
That generation in 2010 with
Radomir Antic on the bench.

00:49:00.060 --> 00:49:05.100
The qualifications went well.
It was a phenomenal group of 15 guys.

00:49:05.780 --> 00:49:10.940
Mister did not change much,
he stuck to the standard team.

00:49:11.180 --> 00:49:14.220
He preparee us to the max.

00:49:14.500 --> 00:49:17.661
In that match against Australia,
when we missed a goal,

00:49:17.797 --> 00:49:20.887
I still don't understand to this day
how we managed not to win.

00:49:21.044 --> 00:49:23.950
It's the most beautiful half time
I've played for the national team.

00:49:24.104 --> 00:49:25.840
Primarily I enjoyed it.

00:49:25.935 --> 00:49:28.972
When we finally reached
the world Championship,

00:49:29.666 --> 00:49:34.794
and beat Germany,
we lost unfortunately to Ghana.

00:49:35.593 --> 00:49:41.553
Yes, we beat Germany and
defeat Australia in the first half.

00:49:42.100 --> 00:49:44.540
If it was 0:3 nobody
would have stolen anything.

00:49:44.740 --> 00:49:48.580
And then we conceded goals
with a header from 13 meters,

00:49:48.780 --> 00:49:50.820
then from a shot from 35 meters.

00:49:51.020 --> 00:49:54.540
We could only run, cry and wonder:
"What happened?"

00:49:54.980 --> 00:49:59.060
Then we score and
due to our excessive desire,

00:49:59.300 --> 00:50:01.660
we missed the impossible.

00:50:02.820 --> 00:50:08.500
We scored one offside goal,
and one penalty in the last second

00:50:08.780 --> 00:50:11.980
was not awarded
to us by the referee.

00:50:12.260 --> 00:50:16.820
And it was identical to the one
he previously awarded to Ghana.

00:50:17.060 --> 00:50:25.020
That's where that generation stopped.
That was all from that generation.

00:50:25.300 --> 00:50:27.300
We could have gone further.

00:50:27.580 --> 00:50:30.260
Draw went very well for us.

00:50:30.580 --> 00:50:35.300
We could have played and fought,
because we did not have a difficult task

00:50:35.620 --> 00:50:38.300
and I am sorry that we did not
take advantage of that.

00:50:38.580 --> 00:50:42.900
If I bring back one game in my career,
that would be... - Australia?

00:50:43.140 --> 00:50:45.740
I'd take all the defeats
just to get that game back

00:50:46.020 --> 00:50:50.580
against Australia, because what we
missed in the first half is unreal.

00:50:50.860 --> 00:50:54.460
Bad luck continued to follow us
during major competitions

00:50:54.740 --> 00:50:59.020
but I was proud and honored
to play for the national team.

00:50:59.260 --> 00:51:03.402
We need to become regular participants
in major competitions,

00:51:03.965 --> 00:51:08.152
and then we will gradually get
a generation that will help us

00:51:08.736 --> 00:51:12.991
regain what we lost
in the match against Australia.

00:51:13.913 --> 00:51:16.960
But we must be constant participants.

00:51:17.619 --> 00:51:21.314
Believe me that it is a special feeling
to be part of the national team

00:51:21.459 --> 00:51:23.059
and to wear that jersey.

00:51:23.223 --> 00:51:25.049
I particularly appreciate
that group of guys.

00:51:25.193 --> 00:51:28.580
Peđa Mijatović, Siniša Mihajlović,
Jugović, Savičević, Stojković,

00:51:28.766 --> 00:51:32.510
Savo, Darko Kovačević, Đorović,
Bata Mirković and Okanović.

00:51:33.201 --> 00:51:36.361
That generation of guys,
who accepted me

00:51:36.900 --> 00:51:40.860
and kept me like this, is priceless.

00:51:41.300 --> 00:51:45.180
It meant a lot to me
that those great people

00:51:45.420 --> 00:51:47.660
appeared in my life then.

00:51:47.940 --> 00:51:53.540
Even today, thank God, I have
excellent relations with everyone.

00:51:53.820 --> 00:51:58.980
I lost Miha, but I jealously keep
him in my heart,

00:51:59.173 --> 00:52:01.693
and with the others,
even after all this time,

00:52:01.894 --> 00:52:04.300
I am in a phenomenal relationship.

00:52:04.688 --> 00:52:06.633
So the national team is
a nice chapter in my life.

00:52:11.420 --> 00:52:14.860
Now, that you’ve touched
on that topic,

00:52:15.180 --> 00:52:19.500
we must mention the deceased
Siniša Mihajlović.

00:52:20.420 --> 00:52:25.300
I have read many texts about
you and him.

00:52:25.940 --> 00:52:29.780
You said a specific word,
that he was, for you,

00:52:30.220 --> 00:52:36.980
the reference point of all
important things in your life.

00:52:37.580 --> 00:52:41.380
Yes, important decisions,
important support.

00:52:41.860 --> 00:52:44.500
The most important thing
is when he says OK.

00:52:44.700 --> 00:52:46.860
And then everything will be OK.

00:52:52.700 --> 00:52:55.660
I spoke to your colleagues
a month ago about this.

00:52:55.980 --> 00:52:57.820
It's hard to talk about.

00:52:58.060 --> 00:53:04.540
As time goes by you realize more
and more who he was.

00:53:04.780 --> 00:53:09.380
And what a great person he was.
Most people were not his equal.

00:53:10.540 --> 00:53:16.500
His ideas, attitudes, his way
of thinking, his honesty and goodness.

00:53:20.820 --> 00:53:26.700
So Miha carries weight in my life.
And a huge emptiness.

00:53:26.940 --> 00:53:33.220
When I dream of him, I want
to know what he wants to tell me.

00:53:33.460 --> 00:53:38.980
I miss one minute with him.
He was big, so big.

00:53:41.620 --> 00:53:50.220
2019 was the entry into Inter's
Hall of Fame. It is a special award.

00:53:50.700 --> 00:53:54.220
How do you look at it now,
after few years?

00:53:54.460 --> 00:54:00.580
Inter is special, you were in.
-Enter... Yes.

00:54:01.020 --> 00:54:11.940
It was the second Hall of Fame awards
ceremony. There were Facchetti, Mazzola,

00:54:12.340 --> 00:54:17.540
names that seriously wrote history,
and in that second round,

00:54:17.860 --> 00:54:20.900
in 2019 I was the midfielder.

00:54:22.580 --> 00:54:26.340
When time passes, only then
do you see how important it is.

00:54:26.580 --> 00:54:32.300
As long as the career lasts,
you don't have time to look back.

00:54:32.500 --> 00:54:34.803
Children grow up fast.

00:54:35.244 --> 00:54:38.724
Soon after "Hi, Dad" it becomes
"Where are you, old man"?

00:54:39.248 --> 00:54:43.568
From the voice of a small baby
to that of an adult.

00:54:43.791 --> 00:54:45.871
A man's career passes.

00:54:47.300 --> 00:54:53.260
When you finish your career and look
back, you realize that it's not so bad.

00:54:53.580 --> 00:54:59.580
It wasn’t easy to achieve that.
Not even counting all the trophies.

00:54:59.860 --> 00:55:02.180
I joked with my colleagues
that my Ana was mad at me

00:55:02.420 --> 00:55:07.500
because we had to buy another
cabinet for all those trophies.

00:55:10.453 --> 00:55:13.964
A lot was won, but it wasn’t easy.

00:55:15.737 --> 00:55:20.300
It required a lot of effort.
In 2019, I entered the Hall of Fame.

00:55:20.700 --> 00:55:27.420
Thanks to voices of the fans.
It wasn't you, me and Zdravko...

00:55:27.660 --> 00:55:32.620
We didn’t agree that Deki
should be in the Hall of Fame. No!

00:55:33.180 --> 00:55:43.059
It was exclusively the fans?
-Yes, only fans. -That's it.

00:55:44.503 --> 00:55:48.801
That's a win.
Being one of them. -Yes.

00:55:54.780 --> 00:56:00.460
Dejan, let's talk about your career
as coach of Crvena Zvezda.

00:56:02.380 --> 00:56:08.180
As far as I know, there were three
championships and 2 cups won?

00:56:08.620 --> 00:56:11.620
You have always played
European matches,

00:56:11.860 --> 00:56:16.980
but not the Champions League
in the group stage.

00:56:17.340 --> 00:56:23.340
You won a lot of points that later
helped Serbia, didn't you?

00:56:23.620 --> 00:56:30.500
But there was still regret
about it. -That's true.

00:56:31.460 --> 00:56:35.020
Is it realistic or not?
I don't know.

00:56:35.260 --> 00:56:38.100
That's exactly what
I wanted to ask you.

00:56:38.340 --> 00:56:41.940
We are used to sometimes
doing unrealistic things.

00:56:42.220 --> 00:56:46.500
Was it realistic for Crvena Zvezda to
win the title of European champion?

00:56:46.740 --> 00:56:52.700
And yes and no! When we talk about
Siniša, Juga, Binić, Pančev,

00:56:52.900 --> 00:56:58.380
Savičević, Belodedić, Najdovski,
Stojanović and all those legends...

00:56:59.040 --> 00:57:04.525
We would say that it is realistic,
but there were a lot of other teams.

00:57:05.877 --> 00:57:10.142
We made it and we were used
to doing miracles in Zvezda,

00:57:10.425 --> 00:57:15.322
something maybe unrealistic.
We were pretty close.

00:57:16.508 --> 00:57:20.644
Three titles, although half or
the whole title is thanks to Vlado,

00:57:20.956 --> 00:57:24.245
because he left me
an advantage of 11 points,

00:57:24.550 --> 00:57:27.917
as well as time and space to find
my way in Crvena Zvezda.

00:57:29.300 --> 00:57:32.740
I don't need anyone to explain what
kind of club it is and how big it is.

00:57:33.060 --> 00:57:38.740
Vladimir Cvetković gave a nice
description of Crvena Zvezda.

00:57:39.020 --> 00:57:43.380
He says that Crvena Zvezda is
as much as you imagined it to be

00:57:43.660 --> 00:57:48.321
before you came to it.
That's how big Crvena Zvezda is.

00:57:48.892 --> 00:57:52.020
So there is no need for anyone to
explain anything about it to me.

00:57:52.300 --> 00:57:59.780
I have learned what Crvena
Zvezda is since my childhood.

00:57:59.980 --> 00:58:06.180
I worked independently as a coach
with Stramaccioni in Serie A for a year.

00:58:06.460 --> 00:58:09.782
It was a nice and
educational experience.

00:58:10.118 --> 00:58:14.532
After that I knew what I wanted
and what I didn't want.

00:58:17.260 --> 00:58:21.540
I had an 11 point lead while
I was figuring things out.

00:58:21.750 --> 00:58:24.070
After that, two double crowns come.

00:58:24.264 --> 00:58:26.558
The round of 16 in the Europa
League is approaching.

00:58:26.705 --> 00:58:28.574
Then the round of 16
in the Europa League.

00:58:28.722 --> 00:58:30.668
For me, that's a phenomenal result.

00:58:30.879 --> 00:58:38.223
These points directly open
the door to the Champions League.

00:58:38.940 --> 00:58:46.165
I failed to enter three times. The first
time I was eliminated on penalties.

00:58:46.443 --> 00:58:50.211
Other times, the details
decided the game.

00:58:50.660 --> 00:58:54.922
Maybe you miss a chance,
miss or score a goal...

00:58:55.165 --> 00:58:59.017
These are all the details
in football that happen.

00:58:59.158 --> 00:59:03.500
They may score in 90th minute,
your own goal instead of extra time.

00:59:03.780 --> 00:59:08.780
You simply become speechless and
experience an emotional breakdown.

00:59:09.060 --> 00:59:12.209
First of all, I am a fan of the
Crvena Zvezda, and then a coach.

00:59:12.403 --> 00:59:15.880
Child of the Crvena Zvezda,
then captain and all that.

00:59:16.130 --> 00:59:18.810
And at that moment I have
an emotional breakdown.

00:59:19.060 --> 00:59:24.980
That's when my work at the Crvena
Zvezde comes to an end.

00:59:25.220 --> 00:59:29.620
Someone will say I ran away.
But what did I run away from?

00:59:30.220 --> 00:59:35.390
Why should I run away from
my city and my Crvena Zvezda?

00:59:36.340 --> 00:59:42.714
It destroyed me. I was in bed
for two days with a fever.

00:59:42.832 --> 00:59:44.632
I couldn't get out of bed.

00:59:44.900 --> 00:59:48.540
You are a man with great
sports and life experience.

00:59:48.780 --> 00:59:55.220
And this is a show that educates
young people about such champions.

00:59:56.540 --> 01:00:03.540
How to pass all that, overcome
the problems and reach the throne?

01:00:03.780 --> 01:00:07.540
Is there a universal formula?

01:00:07.860 --> 01:00:14.142
Can you give us some advice
in a few sentences?

01:00:14.697 --> 01:00:17.857
I will be direct and take my children
as an example.

01:00:18.145 --> 01:00:21.985
I have three sons: Stefan,
he will turn 23, in September.

01:00:22.420 --> 01:00:28.100
Filip, 22, in February
and Aleksandar is 18.

01:00:28.820 --> 01:00:32.900
Stefan was the first to leave
the Inter Academy for Inter.

01:00:33.140 --> 01:00:37.220
It's like a transfer,
you have to pay the Inter Academy.

01:00:37.460 --> 01:00:41.500
And then he started playing
for Inter at 16-17.

01:00:42.700 --> 01:00:48.060
In those years, he represented
Serbia and played for Inter.

01:00:48.420 --> 01:00:50.562
He received an invitation to
the European Championship,

01:00:50.699 --> 01:00:52.835
which was then being
played in Croatia.

01:00:53.046 --> 01:00:55.166
And he decided to quit football.

01:00:57.980 --> 01:01:03.620
I told him to think.
His last name may be a burden.

01:01:03.820 --> 01:01:07.700
Children during that period
don’t know what they want.

01:01:07.940 --> 01:01:09.860
But we have to deal with it.

01:01:10.100 --> 01:01:12.780
They say to him: "You play
because your father is Dejan?"

01:01:13.020 --> 01:01:16.820
And he gives up.
He's just not happy anymore.

01:01:17.060 --> 01:01:20.980
It was difficult for me at first.
I figured he could do that.

01:01:21.260 --> 01:01:27.008
Would he to it for score of 1 or 10,
it depends on him.

01:01:27.265 --> 01:01:30.801
But he will do that
and make a living from it.

01:01:31.113 --> 01:01:34.620
How much he will give up
and how much he will train,

01:01:34.820 --> 01:01:36.580
that depends on him.

01:01:36.820 --> 01:01:39.780
For the first two months it was
difficult to accept his decision,

01:01:39.980 --> 01:01:43.220
but I realized that he is very brave.

01:01:44.100 --> 01:01:47.660
He decided to quit,
because he was’nt happy.

01:01:48.380 --> 01:01:55.331
So, he was not happy, and to me his
happiness is the most important thing.

01:01:55.880 --> 01:02:00.855
Why should I push him by force
and give him obligations?

01:02:01.292 --> 01:02:06.180
He finished school and is on his way.
He knows what football is.

01:02:06.740 --> 01:02:10.980
After that comes Philip. Likewise, from
the Inter Academy, he moves to Inter.

01:02:11.220 --> 01:02:15.760
The goalkeeper, stubborn,
looked up to Stefan.

01:02:16.300 --> 01:02:21.460
"You won't come an inch to me."
He took a guard and doesn't care.

01:02:21.660 --> 01:02:24.460
And Aleksandar moved from
the Inter Academy to Inter.

01:02:24.620 --> 01:02:26.900
And he has his own stance.

01:02:27.100 --> 01:02:32.500
But someone had to be a victim
for the two of them to understand

01:02:32.900 --> 01:02:37.540
what it was all about.
They have a wonderful relationship.

01:02:37.780 --> 01:02:40.340
He really knows what football is.

01:02:40.540 --> 01:02:45.479
And he will definitely pursue football.
I'm waiting for him.

01:02:46.020 --> 01:02:49.220
Filip continued his career at Inter.

01:02:49.500 --> 01:02:52.900
Both Filip and Aleksandar
have a contract with Inter.

01:02:53.100 --> 01:02:55.300
Filip is on loan at Sampdoria.

01:02:56.020 --> 01:03:01.990
Aleksandar is the captain
of the young generation of the Inter.

01:03:02.380 --> 01:03:05.940
He trains with the first team
and has a professional contract.

01:03:06.700 --> 01:03:12.124
The child must be respected.
-That's the point.

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:16.740
If the child isn’t happy,
everything is in vain.

01:03:17.060 --> 01:03:21.206
That's true.
I felt it on my skin, it hurt.

01:03:21.497 --> 01:03:26.112
Maybe it hurt me more than him,
but I can see that he can do it.

01:03:26.390 --> 01:03:32.042
How did we start the interview?
About renunciation.

01:03:33.140 --> 01:03:35.660
It is the starting point
and the ending point.

01:03:35.860 --> 01:03:38.420
How much are you willing
to give up?

01:03:38.940 --> 01:03:47.160
Something was bothering you that
stopped your progress, your growth.

01:03:49.308 --> 01:03:55.495
The pieces have to came together
for you to become someone.

01:03:56.458 --> 01:03:59.956
A lot of giving up,
that's the first and last point.

01:04:01.276 --> 01:04:03.714
Thank you very much.
-The pleasure is mine.

01:04:03.920 --> 01:04:06.252
I hope you won't be late for practice?
-I won't.

